# =============================================================================
# REKINDLE Frontend Environment Variables
# =============================================================================
# Copy this file to .env.local and fill in your actual values
# NEVER commit .env.local to git!

# =============================================================================
# REQUIRED VARIABLES (Phase 0 Fix #1 - Supabase Configuration)
# =============================================================================

# Supabase URL
# Get this from: https://app.supabase.com/project/_/settings/api
# Example: https://abcdefghijklmnop.supabase.co
VITE_SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project-id.supabase.co

# Supabase Anonymous Key (Public Key - safe to expose to frontend)
# Get this from: https://app.supabase.com/project/_/settings/api
# Look for "anon public" key
# Should start with: eyJ...
VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your_supabase_anon_key_here

# =============================================================================
# API Configuration (Phase 0 Fix #2)
# =============================================================================

# Backend API URL
# Development: Leave commented out (will use http://localhost:3001/api)
# Production: REQUIRED or build will fail
# Examples:
#   - Railway: https://your-app.railway.app/api
#   - Render: https://your-app.onrender.com/api
#   - Custom: https://api.yourdomain.com
VITE_API_URL=http://localhost:3001/api

# =============================================================================
# SETUP INSTRUCTIONS
# =============================================================================
#
# 1. Copy this file:
#    cp .env.example .env.local
#
# 2. Get Supabase credentials:
#    - Go to https://app.supabase.com/project/_/settings/api
#    - Copy "Project URL" to VITE_SUPABASE_URL
#    - Copy "anon public" key to VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY
#    - ⚠️ DO NOT use "service_role" key in frontend!
#
# 3. Set API URL:
#    - Development: Leave as http://localhost:3001/api
#    - Production: Update to your deployed backend URL
#
# 4. Build and verify:
#    npm run build
#
#    Should see:
#    ✓ built in XXXms
#
#    Should NOT see:
#    ❌ Missing required Supabase environment variables
#
# =============================================================================
# SECURITY NOTES
# =============================================================================
#
# - NEVER commit .env.local to git (already in .gitignore)
# - Only use "anon public" key, NEVER "service_role" key
# - Service role key grants full database access - backend only!
# - In production, set environment variables in deployment platform:
#   * Vercel: https://vercel.com/docs/environment-variables
#   * Netlify: https://docs.netlify.com/environment-variables/overview/
#   * Railway: https://docs.railway.app/develop/variables
#
# =============================================================================
# TROUBLESHOOTING
# =============================================================================
#
# Build fails with "Missing required Supabase environment variables":
#   → Check that .env.local exists and has VITE_SUPABASE_URL and VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY
#
# Build fails with "Invalid Supabase URL format":
#   → Ensure VITE_SUPABASE_URL starts with https:// and includes .supabase.co
#
# Build fails with "Invalid Supabase anon key format":
#   → Ensure VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY is a JWT starting with "eyJ"
#
# Production build fails with "VITE_API_URL environment variable is required":
#   → Set VITE_API_URL to your deployed backend URL in deployment platform
#
# API calls fail in production:
#   → Verify VITE_API_URL matches your actual backend deployment URL
#   → Check CORS settings in backend allow your frontend domain
#
